&gt; Is there any other workaround for running wiremock as an Azure app service.

As we know that the inbound traffic supports only 80 and 443 ports in Azure app service, To access both spring boot endpoint and wiremock(standalone) from the same port there was the way that is **reverse proxy**.

- For that, first we need to set up some settings check the below.
![enter image description here](https://i.stack.imgur.com/QVrBJ.png)

- Add the application settings, this is required for the reverse proxy to work properly.
![enter image description here](https://i.stack.imgur.com/wYfou.png)

- Specify the IP address and port of Wiremock server to the VNet and hybrid connections also.
![enter image description here](https://i.stack.imgur.com/sx471.png)

- Add inbound security rule set the protocol **TCP**
and ranges to 8085.
Below added a sample template code for better understanding.
```
	private static final String WIREMOCK_HOST = &quot;wiremock-app-service.azurewebsites.net&quot;;
    private static final int WIREMOCK_PORT = 80;

    private final RestTemplate restTemplate;

    public HelloWorldController(RestTemplateBuilder restTemplateBuilder) {
        this.restTemplate = restTemplateBuilder.build();
    }

    @GetMapping(&quot;/hello&quot;)
    public ResponseEntity&lt;String&gt; hello() {
        String url = &quot;http://&quot; + WIREMOCK_HOST + &quot;:&quot; + WIREMOCK_PORT + &quot;/hello&quot;;
        ResponseEntity&lt;String&gt; response = restTemplate.getForEntity(url, String.class);
        return response;
    }
}
```
