In the &quot;where&quot; statement you must not use commas.

your code:

        String query1 = &quot;update hollywood set &quot;
                + &quot;name = :m_name ,&quot;
                + &quot;timing = :m_timing ,&quot;
                + &quot;price = :m_price &quot;
                + &quot;where name = :mname ,&quot;
                + &quot;timing = :mtiming ,&quot;
                + &quot;price = :mprice&quot;;

so it will translate into 

    update hollywood set name = :m_name ,timing = :m_timing ,price = :m_price **where** name = :mname ,timing = :mtiming ,price = :mprice


Notice the `where` keyword in the middle.
so, if you want to update name, timing and price **where** name is mname AND timing = mtiming AND price = mprice you should change into the following:

            String query1 = &quot;update hollywood set &quot;
                    + &quot;name = :m_name ,&quot;
                    + &quot;timing = :m_timing ,&quot;
                    + &quot;price = :m_price &quot;
                    + &quot;where name = :mname AND &quot;
                    + &quot;timing = :mtiming AND &quot;
                    + &quot;price = :mprice&quot;;

this will translate into:
    update hollywood set name = :m_name ,timing = :m_timing ,price = :m_price **where** name = :mname AND timing = :mtiming AND price = :mprice


**Note:** the space after the `AND` keyword is important

